            "heading": "A studio in two disciplines.",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "statement_text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Tectonic — objects built from horizontal logic. Stratified, gridded, load-bearing in form if not in function. Geometry as architecture.</p><p>Biomorphic — objects built from organic mathematics. Spirals, vortices, the curve of a wave arrested mid-motion. Precision applied to what appears imprecise.</p><p>Both disciplines. One standard. Nothing approximated.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["statement_heading", "statement_text"],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "center",
        "content_alignment": "center",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "full_width": false,
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80
      }
    },
